-- Anglo American, Iliad, Naspers May Move Today: South Africa Stocks Preview
-- Nicky Smith
-- 2010-07-23T05:38:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/anglo-american-iliad-naspers-may-move-today-south-africa-stocks-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  
 South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose for a
third day, gaining 440.51, or 1.6 percent, to 28,274.03 at the 5
p.m. close in Johannesburg.  
 Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ): De Beers, the world’s largest
diamond company, reports first-half earnings. Anglo, which owns
about 45 percent of De Beers, climbed 5.50 rand, or 2 percent,
to 283.50 rand.  
 Iliad Africa Ltd.  (ILA SJ): The building-materials
distributor said first-half earnings per share may decline as
much as 32 percent. Iliad dropped 17 cents, or 2.1 percent, to
7.97 rand.  
 Naspers Ltd.  (NPN SJ): The media company hosts an investor
presentation in London. The stock climbed 5.40 rand, or 1.8
percent, to 302.40 rand.  
 Shares or American depositary receipts of the following South
African companies closed as follows:  
 Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) rose 4.1 percent to $18.77.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) added 1.9 percent to $40.02. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) gained 4.2 percent to $59.90. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) gained 3.4 percent to $4.2. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) advanced 3.8 percent to $13.08. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) gained 2 percent to $9.98. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) advanced 7.3 percent to $26.60. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
added 2.5 percent to $4.47. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) gained 4.5
percent to $39.35.  
